text.section:
At the time a consumer applies through a facilitator for a refund anticipation loan, the facilitator orally shall inform the consumer:
That the product is a loan that lasts 1 to 2 weeks;
That if the consumer's tax refund is less than expected, the consumer is liable for the full amount of the refund anticipation loan and must repay any difference;
The amount of the refund anticipation loan fee; and
The annual percentage rate payable on the refund anticipation loan.
